<Item level="0" page="34">
	<Name>Ruler</Name>
	<Price>5 sp</Price>
	<Usage>held in 1 hand</Usage>
	<Description>A ruler is a straight-edged object used for measuring small distances accurately and drawing straight lines.</Description>
</Item>
<Item level="0" page="114">
	<Name>Depth Gauge</Name>
	<Price>1 gp</Price>
	<Bulk>L</Bulk>
	<Hands>2</Hands>
	<Description>This simple tool consists of a small iron weight attached to a thin rope that is marked at regular intervals (typically every foot). It can be used to measure the depth of a hole or body of water by dropping the weight down into unknown depths and counting the markings on the rope. It can also be used as a plumb bob.</Description>
</Item>
